article.description: Christian Lopez passed for 212 yards and two touchdowns and ran for 64 yards and another score to propel North Alabama to a 24-7 victory over Jackson State on Saturday.
article.headline: Lopez leads North Alabama past Jackson State 24-7
article.linkText: Lopez leads North Alabama past Jackson State 24-7
article.story: JACKSON, Miss. -- Christian Lopez passed for 212 yards and two touchdowns and ran for 64 yards and another score to propel North Alabama to a 24-7 victory over Jackson State on Saturday. The Lions (5-3), one of three FCS independent teams, built their lead behind a dominant defense and steady play from Lopez, who completed 14 of 23 passes. North Alabama allowed just four first downs and 65 total yards in building a big lead after three quarters. Lopez scored on a 4-yard run in the first quarter and sandwiched a second-quarter 23-yard TD strike to Donzell Polite and a 42-yard TD toss to Cortez Hall around Chandler Carrera's 23-yard field goal for the three-score advantage. The Tigers (3-3) got on the scoreboard when Keshawn Harper ran it in from the 3-yard line with 10:53 remaining in the fourth quarter. The Lions piled up 365 yards of offense, while holding the Tigers to 163.
